<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920122-0160</DOCNO><DOCID>920122-0160.</DOCID><HL>   BWIP Plans Secondary Offering</HL><DATE>01/22/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BWIP</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>INDUSTRIAL TECHNOLOGY andamp; PRODUCTION, QUALITY CONTROL (ITC)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><NS>BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   LONG BEACH, Calif. -- BWIP Holding Inc. said it filed aregistration statement for a secondary public offering of 5.5million shares of its Class A common stock.   BWIP, a maker of advanced technology pumps and seals, is41%-owned by the New York investment firm of Clayton andamp;Dubilier, which acquired BWIP for $230 million in a 1987management-led leveraged buyout of what was then theindustrial products unit of Borg-Warner Corp. Last year thecompany went public, selling a 33% stake to the public at$14.50 a share. BWIP shares were quoted at $23.25 each, down50 cents, in national over-the-counter trading lateyesterday.</LP><TEXT>   The secondary offering, postponed last November whenClayton andamp; Dubilier withdrew its registration request, is tobe underwritten by Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co. and Donaldson Lufkinandamp; Jenrette Securities Corp. The company said that some of theshares are expected to be sold by management investors, butthat none of these investors are expected to sell more than19% of their shares.</TEXT></DOC>